<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: How do i check all 8 individual bits within a register?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11464&amp;p=131610#p131610"><![CDATA[
This sounds similar to checking parity, except in that case the result would be only bit 0 of that variable that was incremented (which tells if you have an even or odd number of bits).<br /><br />Some code would look like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent"> lda #0<br /> sta count<br /> ldx #8<br /> lda var1<br /><br />@loop:<br /> asl<br /> bcc @skip      ; change to BCS if you want to count number of '0' bits instead<br /> inc count<br />@skip:<br /> dex<br /> bne @loop<br /></div><br /><br />edit: derp<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sat Jul 26, 2014 11:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
